<subSubSection id="04F26550274C1204A96A3543FE09FEA7" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274C1207A96A3543FA08FDB0" blockId="5.[825,1464,539,598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207A96A3543FC15FDD1" bold="true" box="[825,933,539,563]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207A9E33543FC0DFDD1" bold="true" box="[944,957,539,563]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">–</emphasis>
Wing with long narrow, yellowish brown stigma at tip of R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274C1207A9FF3510FC04FDB4" attach="left" box="[940,948,584,598]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">1</subScript>
; stigma reaching beyond level of thickening of
</paragraph>
<caption id="18976653274C1207AA2D3F43FEA0F7AF" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339235" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5339235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339235/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" startId="5.[126,170,2075,2096]" targetBox="[130,1460,698,2014]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274C1207AA2D3F43FEA0F7AF" blockId="5.[126,1464,2075,2125]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">
Figs. 11–13. 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D58274C1207AAAD3F43FE41F7D2" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[254,497,2075,2096]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274C1207AAAD3F43FE41F7D2" box="[254,497,2075,2096]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="22">Hercostomus brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B2274C1207ABAC3F43FDC6F7D2" box="[511,630,2075,2096]" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male: 11, antenna; 12, male genitalia; 13, cercus. iel, inner epandrial lobe; oel, outer epandrial lobe.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274F1204A87637DCFB8EFF79" blockId="6.[549,1086,132,155]" box="[549,1086,132,155]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274F1204A87637DCFC4FFF79" box="[549,1023,132,155]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">THE RAFFLES BULLETIN OF ZOOLOGY</emphasis>
2008
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274F1204AAC73796FE09FEA7" blockId="6.[148,788,206,325]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274F1204AAF53782FF0EFF0A" attach="left" box="[166,190,218,232]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">4+5</subScript>
. R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274F1204AA8C3782FF47FF0A" attach="left" box="[223,247,218,232]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">4+5</subScript>
thickened from basal quarter onward, but narrow again before reaching wing border. Aedeagus with a small denticle more basad in position than in 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D58274F1204A8703656FD20FEC7" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[547,656,270,293]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limosus">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274F1204A8703656FD20FEC7" box="[547,656,270,293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">G. limosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hind femur with tip dorsally darkened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F26550274F1205AAC73635FDC3FAC7" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274F1204AAC73635FEAEFE47" blockId="6.[148,788,365,421]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274F1204AAC73635FEA3FE67" bold="true" box="[148,275,365,389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274F1204AB723635FEC6FE67" bold="true" box="[289,374,365,389]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">– Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="8B109B3E274F1204A8543636FD3AFE67" box="[519,650,366,389]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="3.0999999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="2.8">2.8–3.4 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="8B109B3E274F1204AAC736D6FEAAFE47" box="[148,282,398,421]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8499999999999996" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="2.8499999999999996" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.8">2.8–2.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274F1204AAC73696FABBFE67" blockId="6.[148,788,462,517]" lastBlockId="6.[848,1487,206,389]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
Head metallic green with pale grey pollen. Face wider than first flagellomere, densely grey dusted. Hairs and bristles black. Postocular bristles (including posteroventral hairs) black. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="D4D32A5E274F1204AE5637B6FBE5FEE7" box="[1029,1109,238,261]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" captionTargetId="figure-155@6.[133,1501,535,2051]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–19. Hercostomus lanceolatus, new species, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) yellow; first flagellomere brown, 1.1 times as long as wide, obtuse apically; arista brown, minutely pubescent with very short basal segment. Proboscis brownish yellow with black hairs; palpus brownish yellow with black hairs and black apical bristle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274F1205A90336F6FEBCFC07" blockId="6.[848,1487,430,517]" lastBlockId="7.[126,766,206,997]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
Thorax metallic green with pale grey pollen. Six strong dc, 7–8 pairs of acr short and hair-like; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles (basal pair short and weak). Propleuron with 1 black bristle on lower part. Legs yellow; fore coxa yellow with blackish base, mid and hind coxae black with yellow apex. Hind femur with knee dorsally brown. Fore tarsus from tip of tarsomere 2 onward brownish; mid and hind tarsi from tip of tarsomere 1 onward brownish to brown. Hairs and bristles black. Mid and hind coxae each with 1 exterior bristle. Mid and hind femora each with 1 preapical bristle. Fore tibia with 2 ad and 1 weak pd, apically with 2 bristles; mid tibia with 3 ad, 2 pd and 1 av, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 3 ad, 4 pd and 1 av, apically with 2 bristles. Mid tarsomere 1 with 2 short vs.; hind tarsomere 1 with 1 vs. at base. Hind tarsomere 1 with a black, curved posterior spine at base, directed upwards underneath posterior comb of hind tibia. Relative lengths of femur, tibia and 5 tarsomeres: LI: 1.00: 0.95: 0.50: 0.20: 0.15: 0.10: 0.10; LII: 1.20: 1.37: 0.62: 0.37: 0.27: 0.15: 0.15; LIII: 1.25: 1.55: 0.45: 0.62: 0.45: 0.30: 0.20. Wing (
<figureCitation id="D4D32A5E274E1205AB163596FE21FD07" box="[325,401,718,741]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" captionTargetId="figure-155@6.[133,1501,535,2051]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–19. Hercostomus lanceolatus, new species, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) hyaline, with yellowish to brown stigma near end of R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274E1205AB0E35A2FED5FCEA" attach="left" box="[349,357,762,776]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">1</subScript>
, The stigma consists of a widening of the tip of R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274E1205AAA53442FF4EFCCA" attach="left" box="[246,254,794,808]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">1</subScript>
and a yellowish to brown colouring of the wing membrane. The stigma is narrow (
<figureCitation id="D4D32A5E274E1205ABBB3476FD86FCA7" box="[488,566,814,837]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" captionTargetId="figure-155@6.[133,1501,535,2051]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–19. Hercostomus lanceolatus, new species, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
), widely separated from R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274E1205AA983402FF53FC8A" attach="left" box="[203,227,858,872]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">2+3</subScript>
. It extends beyond the level where the thickening of R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274E1205AAFC3422FF77FC6A" attach="left" box="[175,199,890,904]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">4+5</subScript>
starts. R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274E1205AB783422FEF3FC6A" attach="left" box="[299,323,890,904]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">4+5</subScript>
thickened from basal quarter, to a little before ending in costa. R 
<subScript id="D06C349E274E1205ABD234C2FE29FC4A" attach="left" box="[385,409,922,936]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">4+5</subScript>
and M distinctly parallel apically. M a little thickened at bulge. Squama yellow with black hairs. Halter white.
</paragraph>
<caption id="18976653274F1204AAC53F46FD1BF7AD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" startId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" targetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274F1204AAC53F46FD1BF7AD" blockId="6.[150,1487,2078,2127]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
Figs. 14–19. 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D58274F1204AB403F46FDB7F7D1" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[275,519,2078,2099]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolatus" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274F1204AB403F46FDB7F7D1" box="[275,519,2078,2099]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Hercostomus lanceolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B2274F1204A8403F46FD39F7D1" box="[531,649,2078,2099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274E1205AA2D3356FE28FB27" blockId="7.[126,765,1038,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
Abdomen metallic green with pale grey pollen. Hairs and bristles black. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="D4D32A5E274E1205AB8C3376FDDBFBA7" box="[479,619,1070,1093]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" captionTargetId="figure-155@6.[133,1501,535,2051]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–19. Hercostomus lanceolatus, new species, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Figs. 16–19</figureCitation>
). Epandrium distinctly longer than wide, lateral epandrial lobe acute apically; cercus subrectangular, yellow with yellow hairs; hypandrium short and thick, aedeagus with 1 inner large, brown denticle near apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274E1205AA2D33B5FDC3FAC7" blockId="7.[126,764,1261,1317]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274E1205AA2D33B5FF68FAE7" bold="true" box="[126,216,1261,1285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="8B109B3E274E1205AB3733B6FE07FAE7" box="[356,439,1262,1285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="8B109B3E274E1205A81033B6FD27FAE7" box="[579,663,1262,1285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
. Identical to male in most characters, but stigma absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F26550274E1205AA2D3215FEE2FA67" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB274E1205AA2D3215FEE2FA67" blockId="7.[126,765,1357,1413]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274E1205AA2D3215FEBAFA87" bold="true" box="[126,266,1357,1381]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC9274E1205AA2D3215FF41FA87" bold="true" box="[126,241,1357,1381]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Etymology</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the lanceolate shape of the wing stigma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F26550274E1205AA2D32F5FE24FA27" box="[126,404,1453,1477]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" type="distribution">
